Below from 
https://puppet.com/docs/pe/2019.1/ssh_getting_started_guide.html#ssh-getting-started-guide

The ghoneycutt-ssh module manages SSH keys and removes SSH keys that you aren't managing with Puppet.
This module, available on the Puppet Forge, is one of many modules written by our user community. 
It contains one class: the ssh class. You can learn more about the ghoneycutt-ssh module by visiting the Forge.

puppet module install ghoneycutt-ssh -v 3.61.0